Prodorsum
. Rostrum narrowly rounded. Rostral (
82–90
) and lamellar (
139–155
) setae setiform, slightly barbed. Interlamellar setae short (
16–20
), weakly thickened, smooth, covered by several granules on their surface. Bothridial setae longest setae on prodorsum (
217–233
), thick, weakly dilated in medial part, densely barbed. Exobothridial setae (
32–36
) thin, slightly barbed. Three pairs of prodorsal tubercles (
Da
, 
Ba
, 
Bp
) developed, triangular, round-ended.

Legs . Monodactylous; claws smooth. Lengths of legs and their segments are given in
Table 3
. Formulae of leg setation and solenidia: I (
1–7 – 3–9 – 21
) [ 1–2 – 2 ], II (
1–7 – 4–9 – 18
) [ 1 – 1–2 ], III (
2–4 – 3–9 – 18
) [ 1 – 1 –0], IV (
1–4 – 2–9 – 15
) [ 0–1 –0]; homologies of setae and solenidia indicated in
Table 4
.
